The paper focuses on deep-networks-based hashing for image retrieval, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves regularizing deep networks using fake images generated by a GAN, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on several benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research. Finally, the paper proposes a novel loss function based on maximum-entropy, which is a concept commonly used in machine learning (cs.AI).
